<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="162" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[140,1108,976,1284]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">
This species was detected in the Maritime Provinces (Nova Scotia) in 1997 (
<bibRefCitation author="Majka CG &amp; Smetana A" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" pagination="427 - 434" refId="ref10725" refString="Majka CG, Smetana A (2007) New records of introduced species of Quedius Stephens, 1829 (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) from the Maritime Provinces of Canada. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 109 (2): 427 - 434." type="journal article" year="2007">Majka and Smetana 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Th e new record above, however, establishes that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1908" box="[910,1065,1047,1073]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curtipennis">
<emphasis box="[910,1065,1047,1073]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">Q. curtipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been present in the region from at least 1984. Th e earliest records in North America are from 
<quantity box="[202,291,1117,1143]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.91236" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" unit="in" value="1934.0">1934 in</quantity>
Seattle (
<bibRefCitation author="Smetana A" box="[387,556,1117,1143]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" pagination="1 - 303" refId="ref11244" refString="Smetana A (1971) Revision of the tribe Quediini of America north of Mexico (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada 79: i-vi + 1 - 303." type="journal article" year="1971">Smetana 1971</bibRefCitation>
). In the Palaearctic region it is found throughout Europe east through 
<collectingCountry box="[380,459,1152,1178]" name="Turkey" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">Turkey</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[500,629,1152,1178]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
, as well as in 
<collectingCountry box="[788,890,1153,1179]" name="Morocco" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">Morocco</collectingCountry>
and on the Azores (
<bibRefCitation author="Herman LH" box="[148,312,1187,1213]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" pagination="1 - 4218" refId="ref9869" refString="Herman LH (2001) Catalogue of the Staphylinidae (Insecta: Coleoptera): 1758 to the end of the Second Millennium. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 265: 1 - 4218." type="journal article" year="2001">Herman 2001</bibRefCitation>
, Smetana 2004). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1908" box="[509,725,1187,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curtipennis">
<emphasis box="[509,725,1187,1213]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">Quedius curtipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is often found near settlements in various debris and under stones. Some specimens also have been collected in natural environments in moss and under leaf litter (
<bibRefCitation author="Smetana A" box="[635,804,1258,1284]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" pagination="1 - 303" refId="ref11244" refString="Smetana A (1971) Revision of the tribe Quediini of America north of Mexico (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada 79: i-vi + 1 - 303." type="journal article" year="1971">Smetana 1971</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
